-- China Buys 336,000 Tons of U.S. Soybeans; Japan Buys 157,581 Tons of Corn
-- Alan Bjerga
-- 2010-08-06T13:00:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/china-buys-336-000-tons-of-u-s-soybeans-japan-buys-157-581-tons-of-corn.html

          
          
             U.S. exporters sold 336,000 metric
tons of soybeans to China and 157,581 tons of corn to Japan, the
U.S. Department of Agriculture said today in a statement. The
soybean and corn sales were for delivery in the 2010-2011
marketing year, which begins Sept. 1, the USDA said.  
